parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power steering, brakes, and other essential systems, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
the ignition switch turns off inadvertently
the headlights turn off
and the vehicle loses power steering functionality.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump relay can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or won't start
the fuel pump relay continues to run after shutdown
draining the battery
and the horn may sound randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the sliding door can cause it to open or close unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The sliding door gets stuck in the open position
there is a buzzing noise coming from the lock mechanism
and the door may open or close unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TIPM can cause a range of electrical issues, including the vehicle shutting off while driving, leading to a loss of power steering, brakes, and other essential systems, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
the engine stalls
the windshield wipers and radio turn on and off
and the dash lights flicker.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden deployment of the AHR can cause physical harm to the driver or passenger, including whiplash, head injuries, or loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The AHR deploys unexpectedly
often with a loud pop or boom
and strikes the driver or passenger in the head or neck. The plastic holding mechanism breaks
causing the metal pin or rod to release
and the headrest to extend forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling and shut-off of the engine can cause loss of power steering and brakes, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts off without warning
sometimes while driving at high speeds
and may not restart immediately. The check engine light may or may not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cylinder head can cause engine misfires, leading to loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine misfires
causing the check engine light to illuminate
and may produce a ticking sound. The vehicle may stall or hesitate while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall or shut off, leading to loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off
and the check engine light may illuminate. The vehicle may have difficulty starting or may not start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCM can cause the engine to stall or shut off, leading to loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off
and the check engine light may illuminate. The vehicle may have difficulty starting or may not start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil filter housing assembly can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaks onto the engine
and the check engine light may illuminate.
